DOUG BROWN:  That is Red Wing hockey.  We all play a lot of different positions and a lot of different lines.  We can't worry about where or when or who you are playing with, just you get on the ice, do your best.  It is never an easy series.  You get to professional sports at this level and you are playing for a championship, it is never easy.  It is two good teams out there playing awfully hard and it means an awful lot to everybody, so, nothing comes easy.


